      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The danger lies in how both substances target the same GABA receptors in your brain, causing a synergistic overdose effect that suppresses your brainstem's vital breathing center. While alcohol alone might just dull you, combining it with zolpidem can paralyze your respiratory drive, leading to silent apnea where you stop breathing without waking up. This specific interference with your body's automatic life-support systems is why the combination is medically defined as fatal rather than merely \"extra drowsy.\"",
      "source": "target",
